  { q: `Are onomatopoeia used in formal writing?`, a: `Giongo (actual sounds like ドンドン) appear occasionally in all contexts. Gitaigo (mimetic words like ふわふわ) are common in literature and advertising but generally avoided in academic or legal writing. In business, some are acceptable in casual emails but not formal documents.` },
