  { q: `What's the difference between giongo and gitaigo?`, a: `Giongo (擬音語) represents actual sounds you can hear: ドンドン (banging), ザーザー (heavy rain). Gitaigo (擬態語) represents states, feelings, or textures you can't actually hear: ふわふわ (fluffy), キラキラ (sparkling). A third category, gijougo (擬情語), specifically describes emotions: ワクワク (excited), ドキドキ (heart pounding).` },
